                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker, and live at Stratford. I lost a number of boots and shoes, and spoke to the pawnbroker. On the 20th of January, between eleven and twelve o'clock, Mr. Brasher's man came to me—I know the boots now produced to be mine—they had been taken from the side of my shop-door.</p>
